<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><song><hymn_number>694</hymn_number>
<author>Karen Marra</author>
<lyrics>[V1]
 Dear Jesus You know me
 And I want to start to know you
 I have a dream above everything
 That You put inside of me
 And I wanna make it come true with You

[V2]
 My wings were made for flight
 But I don't know how and when to fly
 So teach me to flap them
 In the air flying above all my fears
 I take your yoke, It's so easy
 Oh your dream is mine
 My burden is yours
 Made of thorns
 And the load is so light
 And the cost of the cross
 Is much easier than my fears

[V3]
 You had a thorny crown of all my fears
 Through those nails went all my pain
 With the thorny crown You felt
 What I feel the burden is upon your head...
 So think of me...

[V4]
 My wings were made for flight...</lyrics>
<title>Thorny fears (Paure spinose)</title>
</song>